This repository is distributed under a **dual-licensing architecture**. Two
disjoint licenses apply to two disjoint classes of content. Reuse must comply
with the license that governs the specific file or fragment in question; the
broader license does NOT subsume the narrower one. Where a single file
contains both classes of content, the intra-file split defined in section 3
controls.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 1.  LICENSING BOUNDARY MATRIX
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A. SOFTWARE LAYER — MIT License (SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT)
   Governs all functional code, build automation, CI/CD configuration,
   structural HTML/CSS scaffolding, repository metadata, and tooling.
   Concretely:
     - Makefile
     - scripts/**                                    (all scripts)
     - .github/workflows/**                          (CI configuration)
     - .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/**                     (issue forms)
     - .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md
     - .gitignore
     - Structural HTML markup and CSS in docs/web/*.html
       (i.e., DOM scaffolding, layout rules, interactive scripts —
        see intra-file split, Section 3)

B. ACADEMIC / RESEARCH LAYER — Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
   International (CC BY 4.0; SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0)
   Governs all scholarly content: the manuscript, its compiled artifact,
   and the scientific prose, equations, figures, and physical /
   thermodynamic models embedded within the popular-science web articles.
   Concretely:
     - docs/paper/OADF_academic_paper.tex
     - docs/paper/OADF_academic_paper.pdf
     - All scientific prose, equations, derivations, tables, figures, and
       physics-model exposition contained within docs/web/*.html
       (see intra-file split, Section 3)
     - Any direct quotation of the above appearing in README.md or any
       other repository documentation.

C. PROJECT METADATA — MIT License (informational documents)
   The following files are repository documentation released under MIT:
     - README.md
     - CONTRIBUTING.md
     - SECURITY.md
     - LICENSE (this file)
     - CITATION.cff (machine-readable metadata)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 2.  SPDX FILE-LEVEL HEADERS (Recommendation)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contributors are encouraged to mark new source files with the appropriate
SPDX header on the first or second line, immediately after a shebang or
encoding declaration when present:

    # SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
or
    % SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0

This is informational; the canonical authority remains Section 1.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 3.  INTRA-FILE SPLIT — Mixed-Content Files (docs/web/*.html)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The HTML articles `mouth_cloud_effect_EN.html` and
`mouth_cloud_effect_HE.html` contain both:

  (a) STRUCTURAL HTML / CSS / JS — DOM hierarchy, layout, styling,
      behaviour. Licensed under the MIT License.

  (b) SCIENTIFIC CONTENT — the explanatory prose, the equations, the
      thermodynamic derivations, the figures, and any direct exposition
      of the physical model presented in OADF_academic_paper.tex.
      Licensed under CC BY 4.0.

Reuse of (a) without (b) does not require academic attribution beyond the
MIT notice. Reuse of (b) — verbatim, translated, paraphrased, or adapted —
requires CC BY 4.0 attribution to Liran Schwartz, including a reference
to the canonical citation in CITATION.cff and the project URL
https://github.com/LiranOG/OADF.

